The course is meant for those language user, who have acquired the language level og A2.2, but who feel that the use of language structures needs some explanation and mastering.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of this course is to develop a learner's skills to use various everyday language structures mainly in written texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student 
- recognises grammar structures in written text in English and is able to find an adequate expression in Estonian;
- can use the present, the past and the future, commonly used prepositions, pronouns and articles;
- uses aqcuired knowledge in oral as well as written communication.
